Durban - The Constitutional Court on Monday found that the appointment of Shaun Abrahams as National Director of Public Prosecutions by former president Jacob Zuma was invalid. In February an application by Corruption Watch seeking to confirm two declaratory orders of constitutional invalidity and an application seeking leave to appeal a High Court ruling that found that Abrahams’s appointment was illegal was heard by the Constitutional Court. Here are five things we know about the judgement handed down by Justice Mbuyiseli Madlanga:     Daily News 